	BOOLEAN variables store either TRUE or FALSE.
	bool is_off = true;
	You can use variables in expressions to create new variables:
	bool is_sleep = is_off;
	You can also use a variable to redefine itself!
	int current_color = 205;
	//How will we change the current_color for when the monitor changes color? 
	current_color = current_color + 10;

	High school math is useless for programming.
	Order of operations is still true for C++ programs!

	the * symbol means multiplication and / means division
	int math = 1+3/(4-1);
}
